---
// canon:publishes-results = false
//
// Index of lab evaluations. Lists and links; publishes no result, finding, or
// conclusion. Adding a headline number here would make this a results page — see
// lab/canon/guard.py.
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Lab" description="Systematic third-party evaluations of AI systems. Pre-registered, hash-bound, replayable.">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 tracking-tight">Lab</h1>
  <p class="text-lg mb-8 max-w-2xl" style="color: var(--color-ink-dim);">
    The methodology engine. Every evaluation publishes a reader-facing writeup
    <em>and</em> the underlying canon envelope, so you can replay the methodology,
    audit the evidence hashes, and cite the finding in a production design review.
    Reviews of external AI systems produce two durable outputs: object-level
    findings and reusable review methodologies that re-enter the knowledge system.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 mt-10">In flight</h2>
  <ul class="space-y-3 max-w-2xl">
    <li>
      <a href="/lab/memory-systems-v1/">Memory systems: Letta vs mem0 vs MemGPT vs Claude memory</a>
      <span class="text-sm ml-2" style="color: var(--color-ink-dim);">(pre-registered)</span>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 mt-10">Planned</h2>
  <ul class="space-y-3 max-w-2xl">
    <li>Agent harness head-to-head on SWE-Bench-Verified (model held constant)</li>
    <li>MCP server implementation survey across the top 50 public servers</li>
    <li>Orchestration framework comparison (LangGraph / CrewAI / Inngest Agents) on a multi-step task suite</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="mt-12 text-sm" style="color: var(--color-ink-dim);">
    <p>
      Evaluation methodology follows the
      <a href="https://synaplex.ai/discovery-framework/0.2.0/">discovery-framework canon</a>:
      every claim is pre-registered with falsification criteria, every evidence record is
      hash-bound to its raw artifact, and every decision cites all known contradictory
      evidence. Post-hoc narrative changes don't happen here.
    </p>
  </div>
</Layout>
